<br>
1.  Staff of Temperate Flux<br>
2.  Circle of Force<br>
3.  Jboots/Tboots/SoW Potions<br>
<br>
Now the fun begins.  Put your damage shield up (Steelskin since Diamond Skin is so damn expensive), cast Levitate, SoW, and Invis.<br>
<br>
Now, you will see their 4 spawn points from above the water.  They are marked by Pillars and little building thingies (don't know what they are called).  When you get to the first pillar, swim directly down and hit F8 to target the first blood.  Now swim towards the other two at the next pillar.  Once you get about halfway there, proc your SoTF to pull the first bunch.  Then once you can see the other two bloods, hit F8 to target one.  Swim directly up, and when your about to surface, proc your staff.  Now you have 4 on you.  In order to keep from loosing them before you get to the shore, walk above the water in zig zags.  Get to the shore, group them up, and kite to your hearts content, rince, and repeat.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzupe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zupe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/25/01 7:03:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling da Bloods</span><hr size=1> There is a great strategy to this. Swimming must be 120+ to get to the surface quicker than them. At 200 I can outrun them under water. The trick to pulling and making it to shore is to buff yourself up, levitate (a must) and sow/jboots/tboots. Once you have that done run to where they spawn and then go underwater to pull. I hit with temp flux on the 2-4 I wanted then look straight up and hit the surface of the water. With levi on you can run across the water and not have to swim. They will kill you if you are swimming running from them, even at 200 skill you will take considerable hits that way. Once on top of the water run to west side of the lake where the columns stick out of the water and you have all kinds of kiting room. I tried east side of the lake, but dumb n00bs would be cute and cast something on my pulls and break the grp. Then you get to listen to an hour of babble of how you got them killed (idiots). Try to keep them in range when you are running to the shore, they will go back or if you go back to get them they will warp on you and that really hurts. Run to the top of ridge at the shore and turn and cast Snare until they come into range (usually as they are just running up out of the water). If you get a resist on snare just run and get a snare on him and then bring them back together and blast away. If I remember correctly about 5 CoF should take them out. Have you lightning strike memmed to kill that jerk that resisted you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Zupe Blastemded<br>
51st Channeler <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uuumuar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uumuar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/25/01 7:08:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to Pull BloodGills?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the input, I am trying to decide between killing Bloodgills in LOIO or goign do the SW corner in EW with ulthokrs and walruses <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/28/01 11:36:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to Pull BloodGills?</span><hr size=1> What level do u have to be to quad the blood gills, i Haed somewhere that they give good exp up till 50 something?!?! thanks for n e aswers<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 12:07:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <