<BR>
<img src=http://www.pcis.net/gurvy/gecko/sig2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirion69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firion69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/25/01 4:24:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to Pull BloodGills?</span><hr size=1> Lol i was here before to get ideas on how to pull them, see TWolf's comment on how to do it, after a few tries I could do it. Now I come back to let you all know its working great, and I notice its TWolf, my guildie who wrote the excellent guide/post Rofl coulda just asked him =)<br>
Anyways, on how to pull them, just read Twolfs post, works great. <br>
<br>
I have some small things worth mentioning tho on these. <br>
<br>
First, when pulling from the one place that is furthest from the beach, you sometimes end up with only 3 gobs with you, this due to youre faster on the surface than the gobs, and them loosing aggro. If youre using 3rd person view you can just look to see how close they are and wait up a bit for them to catch up a bit, or you can swim backwards, hehe the maneuver (sp?) might be a bit tricky for those of you that havent got £33T FPS-game skills =) J/K, but it certainly helps having control of your whereabouts. <br>
<br>
One more thing.<br>
When you have them grouped up nice on the beach and youre going to snare them, pray snare sticks on all of them the first time. If it doesnt, you have to snare the resisters. No big deal. Oh, wait, umm now I snared the resister, where are my other gobs? Grr theyve lost aggro on you, and either roams the beach killing lowbies (very bad) or went back to their spawns (not that bad)<br>
if 2 or more resists, I just run them in circles till BoF wears off. True, its  timeconsuming but 2 resisters are rare. If one resists, I try to resnare it a.s.a.p. and more importantly, get back to where I lest the snared gobbos to reaggro them. After that, I bunch them up, cast about 3 aoes, then resnare them all, and continue the slaughter. At level  44 with maxed int and almost 300 managear, you aint runnning out of mana on them, I usually start the kite at half a bub from FM, just to not get any more downtime then necessary.<br>
One more bonus to this place is that there usualy is chanters breezing/calritying in the mill, hehe with jBoots and cla, youre PLing yourself here =) I made a yellow in 44 and 3 yellows in 45 (planes here I come! ) in one day of kiting these. You get a little more than half a blue per kite in hell 45 off them, and considering it takes 4 bubs maybe a little less to kill 4, its very very good xp (not that you didnt know it but well =)   )<br>
In comparison I hunted Giants for well say an hour at least, maybe up to 2 hours in EW and GD, i got half a blue... man id hate not being able to quad.<br>
